The paper discusses a method for training neural networks to be robust to subsequent pruning, which is a common technique for achieving sparsity in neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which further supports these sub-categories as likely candidates.
